## How the relationship between size (g/mm^2) of Adalia bipunctata and the vigour/condition of long beetles varies between colour morphs. 

I hypothesised that the relation between the colour morph of A.bibucta and the vigour/condition of long beetles may vary with the colour morph of the species. 
To test the hypothesis, I compared size as a continuous variable and colour morph as a factorial predictor the interaction term is the right time is seconds as a count. This was fitted as generalised linear model with a poison error distribution and a log linker, A quasi likelihood model was fitted to account for the over-dispersion of the data. 
A significant interaction effect of the size and colour morph (X^2 ~ 1, 76=4249.0 p<0.05) was calculated. So, the relation between increasing the size and right mean is different in the differing colour morphs. 
When the size is zero for M the log right time is -4.250 and when the body size is zero for T the log vigour/condition 5.1846. The difference between the intercept is 9.435. The difference between the M and T intercept difference is 9.345. The log increase in the right time when the body size increases by 1 in M is 9034.753. The log increases in right time when the body size increases by in in T is -2966.6699. There a significant difference of the rate of change of the M and T colour morphs. For T as the size increases the vigour/condition decreases, for M as the size increases the right time decreases (F= 40.334 p<0.05 R^2T=0.1005853, R^2M = 0.1579649). 
Little to research has been conducted investigating the relationship between vigour/condition and colour morphs. 

